1
00:00:07,583 --> 00:00:08,625
- KATARA: Water.

2
00:00:09,834 --> 00:00:10,750
Earth.

3
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:12,667
Fire.

4
00:00:13,792 --> 00:00:14,750
Air.

5
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:20,375
Long ago, the four nations
lived together in harmony.

6
00:00:20,417 --> 00:00:23,458
Then, everything changed
when the Fire Nation attacked.

7
00:00:24,875 --> 00:00:27,458
Only the Avatar,
master of all four elements,

8
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:29,000
could stop them.

9
00:00:29,041 --> 00:00:31,125
But when the world
needed him most, he vanished.

10
00:00:32,458 --> 00:00:34,667
A hundred years passed,
and my brother and I discovered

11
00:00:34,709 --> 00:00:37,875
the new Avatar,
an Airbender named Aang.

12
00:00:37,917 --> 00:00:39,959
And although
his airbending skills are great,

13
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,625
he has a lot to learn before
he's ready to save anyone.

14
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:43,917
- Ugh!

15
00:00:43,959 --> 00:00:47,041
- KATARA: But I believe
Aang can save the world.

16
00:00:47,083 --> 00:00:50,583
♪

17
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:57,375
- We won't be able
to mount a massive invasion

18
00:00:57,417 --> 00:00:59,000
without the Earth King's armies.

19
00:00:59,041 --> 00:01:00,834
But the solar eclipse
will still leave

20
00:01:00,875 --> 00:01:02,667
the Fire Nation vulnerable.

21
00:01:02,709 --> 00:01:04,583
- So we're planning
a smaller invasion.

22
00:01:04,625 --> 00:01:06,542
Just a rag-tag team
of our friends and allies

23
00:01:06,583 --> 00:01:07,917
from around the Earth Kingdom.

24
00:01:07,959 --> 00:01:10,792
- It's better for now that
no one knows I'm alive.

25
00:01:10,834 --> 00:01:14,208
- You used to be the pride
of the Fire Nation.

26
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:16,667
Now look at you.

27
00:01:16,709 --> 00:01:19,375
Look what you've become.

28
00:01:19,417 --> 00:01:21,709
- Look, you guys keep telling me
I need to sleep.

29
00:01:21,750 --> 00:01:22,875
But I can't!

30
00:01:22,917 --> 00:01:24,834
The invasion's tomorrow!

31
00:01:24,875 --> 00:01:27,250
- You've been training for this
since the day we met.

32
00:01:27,291 --> 00:01:28,542
- You can do this.

33
00:01:28,583 --> 00:01:29,834
You're ready.

34
00:01:29,875 --> 00:01:31,834
- During the meeting,
I was the perfect prince,

35
00:01:31,875 --> 00:01:33,875
the son my father wanted.

36
00:01:33,917 --> 00:01:35,500
But I wasn't me.

37
00:01:35,542 --> 00:01:38,500
- Evil and good are always
at war inside you, Zuko.

38
00:01:38,542 --> 00:01:42,083
It is your nature, your legacy.

39
00:01:42,125 --> 00:01:45,458
Born in you along
with all this strife

40
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:50,834
is the power to restore
balance to the world.

41
00:01:50,875 --> 00:01:54,208
♪

42
00:02:09,125 --> 00:02:10,417
- Top of the morning, Momo!

43
00:02:10,458 --> 00:02:12,166
- Sounds like you slept well.

44
00:02:12,208 --> 00:02:13,375
- Like a baby moose lion.

45
00:02:13,417 --> 00:02:15,750
I'm ready to face the Fire Lord.

46
00:02:15,792 --> 00:02:17,792
- So what's your strategy
for taking him down?

47
00:02:17,834 --> 00:02:19,625
Going to get your glow on
and hit him with

48
00:02:19,667 --> 00:02:21,208
a little Avatar State action?

49
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,667
- I can't.

50
00:02:22,709 --> 00:02:24,166
When Azula shot me
with lightning,

51
00:02:24,208 --> 00:02:26,792
my seventh chakra was locked,
cutting off my connection

52
00:02:26,834 --> 00:02:30,125
to all the cosmic energy
in the Universe.

53
00:02:30,166 --> 00:02:31,709
- You know what I just heard?

54
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:34,792
Blah-blah spiritual mumbo jumbo,
blah-blah something about space.

55
00:02:36,125 --> 00:02:37,792
- Oh no.

56
00:02:37,834 --> 00:02:41,542
Sokka, do you think the fog
will delay the invasion?

57
00:02:41,583 --> 00:02:44,500
- No, that is the invasion.

58
00:02:44,542 --> 00:02:49,750
- ♪

59
00:02:55,125 --> 00:02:56,792
- You made it, Dad!

60
00:02:56,834 --> 00:02:59,333
- Were you able to locate
everyone I told you to find?

61
00:02:59,375 --> 00:03:02,041
- I did, but I'm
a little worried, Sokka.

62
00:03:02,083 --> 00:03:05,041
Some of these men
aren't exactly the warrior type.

63
00:03:05,083 --> 00:03:07,250
- Whooo-wheee.

64
00:03:07,291 --> 00:03:09,542
This place ain't nothing
like a swamp.

65
00:03:09,583 --> 00:03:11,417
What'd you reckon that is, Tho?

66
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:13,041
Some sort of Fire Nation
exploding trap

67
00:03:13,083 --> 00:03:14,375
that would eat ya?

68
00:03:14,417 --> 00:03:16,041
- It's just a rock, Due.

69
00:03:16,083 --> 00:03:18,667
- Well, I'll be.

70
00:03:18,709 --> 00:03:20,583
- Is it just me,
or are those fellas

71
00:03:20,625 --> 00:03:22,500
a little loose in the leaf hat?

72
00:03:22,542 --> 00:03:25,250
- I just wish
they would wear pants.

73
00:03:25,291 --> 00:03:27,291
- Pants are an illusion.

74
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,417
And so is death.

75
00:03:31,458 --> 00:03:35,041
- HARU: Hi, Katara.

76
00:03:35,083 --> 00:03:37,375
- Haru, it's so good to see you.

77
00:03:37,417 --> 00:03:38,959
- Toph, this is Haru.

78
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,291
When we met him, his town was
controlled by the Fire Nation.

79
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:43,000
So we had to hide
his Earth-bending.

80
00:03:43,041 --> 00:03:46,458
- Katara inspired me and my
father to take back our village.

81
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:49,375
- You helped us find
our courage, Katara.

82
00:03:49,417 --> 00:03:53,375
Now we're here to help you.

83
00:03:53,417 --> 00:03:55,792
- No way. Is that--

84
00:03:55,834 --> 00:03:59,041
- Hippo happy
to see Blind Bandit!

85
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:00,917
- You guys here for a rematch?

86
00:04:00,959 --> 00:04:02,583
- Negatory.

87
00:04:02,625 --> 00:04:05,583
The Boulder and The Hippo
no longer fight

88
00:04:05,625 --> 00:04:07,417
for others' entertainment.

89
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:11,000
Now, we fight for our Kingdom!

90
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:12,709
- Sweet!

91
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,667
- ♪

92
00:04:14,709 --> 00:04:16,458
- [crash]

93
00:04:18,041 --> 00:04:21,709
- [coughing]

94
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:27,625
- Was that a new invention?

95
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:28,917
- Yes.

96
00:04:28,959 --> 00:04:32,709
But unfortunately,
the incendiary capabilities

97
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:35,667
of peanut sauce
proved to be a failure.

98
00:04:35,709 --> 00:04:37,500
- You're making
peanut sauce bombs?

99
00:04:37,542 --> 00:04:39,041
- They're destructive.

100
00:04:39,083 --> 00:04:40,458
- And delicious!

101
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:43,125
- BOTH: [slurps and laughs]

102
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:45,750
- Were you able to complete work
on the plans I sent you?

103
00:04:45,792 --> 00:04:47,166
- Yes, I was.

104
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:50,417
And I think the Fire Nation
would be quite surprised.

105
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:52,750
- Aang, my dad and I
made this for you.

106
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:56,458
- ♪

107
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,875
- A new glider!

108
00:04:57,917 --> 00:04:59,375
This is amazing.

109
00:04:59,417 --> 00:05:03,417
- And as a special feature,
I added a snack compartment.

110
00:05:05,542 --> 00:05:07,750
- Oh well, I'm sure
that will come in handy.

111
00:05:10,959 --> 00:05:14,041
- I bet you're tired of
being in that cell, old man.

112
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:16,000
Well, too bad.

113
00:05:16,041 --> 00:05:19,041
You're never stepping
outside these walls again.

114
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:20,875
- Breakfast.

115
00:05:20,917 --> 00:05:22,000
- Careful, Ming.

116
00:05:22,041 --> 00:05:23,458
Don't get too close.

117
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,417
His stench will
knock you right out.

118
00:05:25,458 --> 00:05:26,792
[chuckles]

119
00:05:28,542 --> 00:05:30,417
- Ming: I snuck in
some white jade tea.

120
00:05:30,458 --> 00:05:33,291
I know you like rare teas.

121
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,041
- Thank you, Ming.

122
00:05:35,083 --> 00:05:39,792
Ever since I was put in here,
you have been very kind to me.

123
00:05:39,834 --> 00:05:45,041
- ♪

124
00:05:45,083 --> 00:05:46,291
- [gulps nervously]

125
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:48,208
- Don't worry, you'll do great.

126
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:51,417
- [deep breath]

127
00:05:51,458 --> 00:05:52,792
Good morning, everyone!

128
00:05:52,834 --> 00:05:53,709
Ah!

129
00:05:56,417 --> 00:05:58,166
Um...

130
00:05:58,208 --> 00:06:02,208
So, as you know, today
we're invading the Fire Nation.

131
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:03,625
I mean I know you know that.

132
00:06:03,667 --> 00:06:05,125
Because otherwise why else
would you be here.

133
00:06:05,166 --> 00:06:06,583
[laughs] Anyway...

134
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:11,583
The Fire Lord's palace is here.

135
00:06:11,625 --> 00:06:13,959
Uh no, uh wait--uh
wait--uh wait, it's here.

136
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,834
And, uh, there's
an eclipse today.

137
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,875
And Aang's going
to fight the Fire Lord.

138
00:06:17,917 --> 00:06:20,083
And the Firebenders
won't have any fire to use,

139
00:06:20,125 --> 00:06:21,750
so that's good for us.

140
00:06:21,792 --> 00:06:26,750
And um--I'm sorry, let me
start at the beginning.

141
00:06:26,792 --> 00:06:28,458
Katara and I discovered
Aang frozen in an iceberg.

142
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:30,875
Now I didn't like Aang at first,
but I grew to love him

143
00:06:30,917 --> 00:06:32,500
over time, then we went over
to the Southern Air Temple,

144
00:06:32,542 --> 00:06:34,125
where Aang used to live,
and then we met Suki,

145
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:36,875
who is a Kyoshi warrior.
- Wow, when he says beginning,

146
00:06:36,917 --> 00:06:38,458
he means
the beginning beginning.

147
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:40,917
- --got Haru arrested, and
then now he's grown a mustache.

148
00:06:40,959 --> 00:06:43,583
Which if you look in the front--
- Thank you, Sokka.

149
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:46,333
It's okay, why don't
you take a break?

150
00:06:46,375 --> 00:06:49,375
Let me just clarify
a few points for everyone.

151
00:06:49,417 --> 00:06:52,083
Today is the Day of Black Sun.

152
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:54,625
And I want to thank you all
for your self sacrifice

153
00:06:54,667 --> 00:06:56,583
and your courage.

154
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:58,542
There are two steps
to the invasion.

155
00:06:58,583 --> 00:07:01,959
A naval stage
and then a land stage.

156
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,125
To gain sea access
to the Fire Nation capital,

157
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:08,333
we have to get past
our first major obstacle here.

158
00:07:08,375 --> 00:07:10,208
The Great Gates of Azulon.

159
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:13,041
Next, we hit the land,
and we hit hard.

160
00:07:13,083 --> 00:07:14,625
We must fight
past their battlements

161
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:16,917
and secure the plaza tower.

162
00:07:16,959 --> 00:07:19,709
Once we do that,
it's up to the royal palace.

163
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:22,417
At that point,
the eclipse will begin.

164
00:07:22,458 --> 00:07:24,208
- Excuse me.

165
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:26,709
The Boulder is confused.

166
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:30,041
Isn't the point to invade
during the eclipse?

167
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:32,875
When the Firebenders
are powerless?

168
00:07:32,917 --> 00:07:35,000
- The eclipse
only last eight minutes.

169
00:07:35,041 --> 00:07:37,000
Not enough time
for the whole invasion.

170
00:07:37,041 --> 00:07:40,166
And the royal palace is heavily
guarded by Firebenders.

171
00:07:40,208 --> 00:07:43,458
So that's where we'll need
the eclipse advantage the most.

172
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:45,625
When this is finished,
the Avatar

173
00:07:45,667 --> 00:07:48,041
would have defeated
the Fire Lord.

174
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:50,875
We would have control
of the Fire Nation capital.

175
00:07:50,917 --> 00:07:54,125
And this war will be over!

176
00:07:54,166 --> 00:08:00,083
- [crowd cheering]

177
00:08:00,125 --> 00:08:03,208
- ♪

178
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,458
- [roars]

179
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:20,583
- ♪

180
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:29,250
- [sheep baas]

181
00:08:29,291 --> 00:08:35,083
- ♪

182
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:48,625
♪

183
00:08:57,041 --> 00:08:58,542
- We've been looking
everywhere for you.

184
00:08:58,583 --> 00:09:00,417
The boats are ready to leave.

185
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:02,041
- I messed up, Aang.

186
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:03,500
- What?

187
00:09:03,542 --> 00:09:05,667
- The invasion plan
was my moment of truth.

188
00:09:05,709 --> 00:09:07,917
And I completely flopped it.

189
00:09:07,959 --> 00:09:11,000
I just...fell apart.

190
00:09:11,041 --> 00:09:13,542
- Sokka, that speech wasn't
your moment of truth.

191
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:15,000
That was just public speaking,

192
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:17,125
and nobody's really good
at that.

193
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:18,583
- My dad is.

194
00:09:18,625 --> 00:09:21,333
He explained the plan perfectly
and inspired everyone.

195
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:23,542
Like a real leader should.

196
00:09:23,583 --> 00:09:24,834
- Look, your moment of truth

197
00:09:24,875 --> 00:09:27,083
isn't going to be
in front of some map.

198
00:09:27,125 --> 00:09:29,834
It's going to be out there
on the battlefield.

199
00:09:29,875 --> 00:09:31,667
- You seem so confident
about everything.

200
00:09:31,709 --> 00:09:33,458
How do you know
we're going to win?

201
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:36,583
- Because I already failed
the world once at Ba Sing Se.

202
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:38,333
I won't let myself fail again.

203
00:09:38,375 --> 00:09:42,041
- ♪

204
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:45,834
- Bato: There they are.

205
00:09:45,875 --> 00:09:47,875
The Great Gates of Azulon.

206
00:09:47,917 --> 00:09:50,125
- Katara: I don't
see any gates.

207
00:09:50,166 --> 00:09:51,792
- Katara,
you and the Swamp-Benders

208
00:09:51,834 --> 00:09:53,458
whip up a fog cover.

209
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:55,834
- We'll sneak by that statues
just like we sneaked by

210
00:09:55,875 --> 00:09:57,667
that fire navy blockade.

211
00:09:57,709 --> 00:10:00,792
- ♪

212
00:10:08,375 --> 00:10:10,750
- Keep it up,
we're almost through.

213
00:10:10,792 --> 00:10:15,250
- [alarming ringing]

214
00:10:17,291 --> 00:10:21,208
- [fire blazing]

215
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:26,125
- ♪

216
00:10:34,083 --> 00:10:35,917
- [fire blazing]

217
00:10:35,959 --> 00:10:41,125
- ♪

218
00:10:41,166 --> 00:10:43,250
- [motors revving]

219
00:10:43,291 --> 00:10:44,625
- Everyone below deck.

220
00:10:46,583 --> 00:10:48,583
Let's hope your invention works.

221
00:10:48,625 --> 00:10:54,542
- ♪

222
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:10,667
- [crash]

223
00:11:13,417 --> 00:11:15,291
- No one's on board, Sir.

224
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:16,667
- Where'd they go?

225
00:11:16,709 --> 00:11:22,625
♪

226
00:11:28,583 --> 00:11:30,709
- You really outdone
yourself this time, son.

227
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:31,834
- Yeah.

228
00:11:31,875 --> 00:11:33,917
Congratulations, Sokka.

229
00:11:33,959 --> 00:11:37,458
You managed to invent a worst
way of travel than flying.

230
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,792
- Helmet?

231
00:11:38,834 --> 00:11:39,875
- [vomits]

232
00:11:39,917 --> 00:11:41,417
- Well, I just came up
with the idea.

233
00:11:41,458 --> 00:11:42,834
The Mechanist did all the work.

234
00:11:42,875 --> 00:11:44,792
- But don't sell
yourself short, my boy.

235
00:11:44,834 --> 00:11:48,125
It was your idea
to use water-bending

236
00:11:48,166 --> 00:11:50,709
to make the subs sink and float.

237
00:11:50,750 --> 00:11:51,917
Brilliant!

238
00:11:51,959 --> 00:11:53,667
Though your original designs

239
00:11:53,709 --> 00:11:56,917
were a bit difficult
to decipher.

240
00:11:56,959 --> 00:12:00,667
Unfortunately, there is
one problem I couldn't fix.

241
00:12:00,709 --> 00:12:03,166
The subs have
a limited air supply.

242
00:12:03,208 --> 00:12:07,166
Before we land on the beaches,
we'll need to resurface.

243
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:12,625
- Lunchtime, General Iroh.

244
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:15,208
And this time, I brought you
an extra bowl of rice.

245
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:17,417
- Thank you, Ming.

246
00:12:17,458 --> 00:12:20,250
Your little gestures of kindness

247
00:12:20,291 --> 00:12:23,959
have made my days in prison
bearable.

248
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:27,583
I think you should take
the rest of the day off.

249
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:30,500
- What?
- You don't look well.

250
00:12:30,542 --> 00:12:33,875
Maybe you should
go home and rest.

251
00:12:33,917 --> 00:12:35,834
- No, I feel fine.

252
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:37,125
- Trust me.

253
00:12:37,166 --> 00:12:41,041
It is better that you are
not here this afternoon.

254
00:12:41,083 --> 00:12:46,709
♪

255
00:12:57,250 --> 00:12:59,917
- So, this is it, huh?

256
00:12:59,959 --> 00:13:01,500
- Are you ready
for the Fire Nation to know

257
00:13:01,542 --> 00:13:03,166
the Avatar's alive?

258
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:04,917
- I'm ready.

259
00:13:04,959 --> 00:13:09,291
- ♪

260
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:12,375
- I hope you kick some serious
Fire Lord butt, twinkle toes.

