00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:57,709
- No. I want to press forward
with the others.

544
00:29:01,625 --> 00:29:04,542
- [whistling]

545
00:29:04,583 --> 00:29:06,291
[gasps]

546
00:29:06,333 --> 00:29:09,166
- ♪

547
00:29:09,208 --> 00:29:11,208
- The Fire Lord's chamber
is that way down the hall

548
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:14,000
to the left and up the stairs.
You can't miss it.

549
00:29:14,041 --> 00:29:15,709
- Thanks.

550
00:29:19,333 --> 00:29:22,000
- [sighs]

551
00:29:22,041 --> 00:29:23,291
[whistles]

552
00:29:23,333 --> 00:29:26,166
- ♪

553
00:29:26,208 --> 00:29:28,208
- Only 30 seconds
until the total eclipse.

554
00:29:28,250 --> 00:29:32,166
- ♪

555
00:29:32,208 --> 00:29:34,917
- [deep breathing]

556
00:29:34,959 --> 00:29:36,333
I'm ready.

557
00:29:36,375 --> 00:29:39,041
I'm ready to face the Fire Lord.

558
00:29:39,083 --> 00:29:42,500
- [door opens]

559
00:29:42,542 --> 00:29:44,959
- So, you are alive after all.

560
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,000
- ♪

561
00:29:47,041 --> 00:29:49,291
- I had a hunch
that you survived.

562
00:29:49,333 --> 00:29:50,500
But it doesn't matter,

563
00:29:50,542 --> 00:29:52,375
I've known about the invasion
for months.

564
00:29:52,417 --> 00:29:56,709
- ♪

565
00:29:58,375 --> 00:29:59,917
- I'm ready to face you.

566
00:29:59,959 --> 00:30:04,208
- ♪

567
00:30:04,250 --> 00:30:07,208
- Prince Zuko,
what are you doing here?

568
00:30:07,250 --> 00:30:09,625
- ♪

569
00:30:13,041 --> 00:30:17,583
- ♪

570
00:30:21,542 --> 00:30:23,709
- The eclipse is starting!

571
00:30:23,750 --> 00:30:25,750
Put on your eclipse glasses.

572
00:30:25,792 --> 00:30:30,583
- ♪

573
00:30:38,417 --> 00:30:40,709
- Why are you here?

574
00:30:40,750 --> 00:30:42,750
- I'm here to tell the truth.

575
00:30:42,792 --> 00:30:46,417
- Telling the truth
during the middle of an eclipse.

576
00:30:46,458 --> 00:30:48,125
This should be interesting.

577
00:30:53,667 --> 00:30:55,875
- First of all, in Ba Sing Se,

578
00:30:55,917 --> 00:30:59,000
it was Azula who took down
the Avatar, not me.

579
00:30:59,041 --> 00:31:01,583
- Why would she
lie to me about that?

580
00:31:01,625 --> 00:31:03,208
- Because the Avatar
is not dead.

581
00:31:03,250 --> 00:31:04,583
He survived.

582
00:31:04,625 --> 00:31:05,959
- What?

583
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,417
- In fact, he's probably
is leading this invasion.

584
00:31:08,458 --> 00:31:10,125
He could be on us right now.

585
00:31:10,166 --> 00:31:11,709
- Get out!

586
00:31:11,750 --> 00:31:14,250
Get out of my sight right now
if you know what's good for you.

587
00:31:14,291 --> 00:31:15,375
- That's another thing.

588
00:31:15,417 --> 00:31:17,458
I'm not taking orders
from you anymore.

589
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:19,834
- You will obey me

590
00:31:19,875 --> 00:31:22,667
or this defiant breath
will be your last!

591
00:31:24,667 --> 00:31:26,250
- Think again!

592
00:31:26,291 --> 00:31:29,250
I am going to speak my mind,
and you are going to listen!

593
00:31:29,291 --> 00:31:32,041
- ♪

594
00:31:32,083 --> 00:31:33,250
- Where is he?

595
00:31:33,291 --> 00:31:35,166
Where is the Fire Lord?

596
00:31:35,208 --> 00:31:37,375
- Hm, you mean I'm not
good enough for you?

597
00:31:37,417 --> 00:31:39,959
You're hurting my feelings.

598
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:42,583
- Stop wasting our time
and give us the information.

599
00:31:42,625 --> 00:31:45,500
You're powerless right now, so
you're in no position to refuse.

600
00:31:45,542 --> 00:31:47,166
- And stick to the truth.

601
00:31:47,208 --> 00:31:49,458
I'll be able to tell
if you're lying.

602
00:31:49,500 --> 00:31:50,667
- Are you sure?

603
00:31:50,709 --> 00:31:53,083
I'm a pretty good liar.

604
00:31:53,125 --> 00:31:55,959
I am a 400-foot-tall
purple platypus bear

605
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:59,709
with pink horns
and silver wings.

606
00:31:59,750 --> 00:32:01,166
- Okay, you're good, I admit it.

607
00:32:04,291 --> 00:32:07,000
But you really ought to consider
telling the truth anyway.

608
00:32:07,041 --> 00:32:09,959
- ♪

609
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:15,000
- [crash]

610
00:32:15,041 --> 00:32:18,000
- When I left Ba Sing Se,
I brought home some souvenirs.

611
00:32:18,041 --> 00:32:20,250
- ♪

612
00:32:20,291 --> 00:32:21,917
- Dai Li agents.

613
00:32:21,959 --> 00:32:26,083
- ♪

614
00:32:35,709 --> 00:32:37,583
- Surround the periphery!

615
00:32:37,625 --> 00:32:40,959
We have to secure the palace
by the time the eclipse is over.

616
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:44,083
Otherwise, we'll be in
for the fight of our lives.

617
00:32:49,083 --> 00:32:50,500
- Stop!

618
00:32:50,542 --> 00:32:52,750
Surrender peacefully,
and we won't harm you.

619
00:32:52,792 --> 00:32:54,333
- We'll never surrender.

620
00:32:54,375 --> 00:32:59,583
- ♪

621
00:32:59,625 --> 00:33:01,250
- Er, okay, we surrender.

622
00:33:01,291 --> 00:33:03,458
- ♪

623
00:33:03,500 --> 00:33:04,625
- There it is.

624
00:33:04,667 --> 00:33:06,709
The Fire Nation royal palace.

625
00:33:06,750 --> 00:33:08,458
We've come so far.

626
00:33:08,500 --> 00:33:10,041
- It's not over yet.

627
00:33:10,083 --> 00:33:13,000
- ♪

628
00:33:13,041 --> 00:33:14,667
- For so long, all I wanted

629
00:33:14,709 --> 00:33:17,291
was for you to love me,
to accept me.

630
00:33:17,333 --> 00:33:19,208
I thought it was my honor t
hat I wanted.

631
00:33:19,250 --> 00:33:22,625
But really, I was just
trying to please you.

632
00:33:22,667 --> 00:33:27,375
You, my father, who banished me
just for talking out of turn.

633
00:33:27,417 --> 00:33:30,583
My father, who challenged me--
a 13-year-old boy--

634
00:33:30,625 --> 00:33:32,125
to an Agni Kai.

635
00:33:32,166 --> 00:33:35,125
How can you possibly
justify a duel with a child?

636
00:33:35,166 --> 00:33:37,250
- It was to teach you respect.

637
00:33:37,291 --> 00:33:38,166
- It was cruel!

638
00:33:38,208 --> 00:33:39,375
And it was wrong!

639
00:33:39,417 --> 00:33:41,041
- Then you've learned nothing.

640
00:33:41,083 --> 00:33:43,792
- No, I've learnt everything!

641
00:33:43,834 --> 00:33:46,083
And I've had to learn it on my
own.

642
00:33:46,125 --> 00:33:48,208
Growing up, we were taught
that the Fire Nation

643
00:33:48,250 --> 00:33:50,709
was the greatest civilization
in history.

644
00:33:50,750 --> 00:33:53,500
And somehow, the war was our way
of sharing our greatness

645
00:33:53,542 --> 00:33:55,667
with the rest of the world.

646
00:33:55,709 --> 00:33:58,166
What an amazing lie that was.

647
00:33:58,208 --> 00:34:01,375
The people of the world are
terrified by the Fire Nation!

648
00:34:01,417 --> 00:34:04,125
They don't see our greatness,
they hate us!

649
00:34:04,166 --> 00:34:05,542
And we deserve it.

650
00:34:05,583 --> 00:34:08,166
We've created an era
of fear in the world.

651
00:34:08,208 --> 00:34:11,166
And if we don't want the world
to destroy itself,

652
00:34:11,208 --> 00:34:15,834
we need to replace it with
an era of peace and kindness.

653
00:34:15,875 --> 00:34:18,083
- [laughing]

654
00:34:18,125 --> 00:34:22,333
Your Uncle has gotten to you,
hasn't he?

655
00:34:22,375 --> 00:34:24,834
- Yes. He has.

656
00:34:28,166 --> 00:34:30,333
- [crash]

657
00:34:30,375 --> 00:34:33,667
♪

658
00:34:36,166 --> 00:34:38,625
- [rock crumbling]

659
00:34:38,667 --> 00:34:43,000
♪

660
00:35:03,542 --> 00:35:04,917
- [crash]

661
00:35:04,959 --> 00:35:07,041
- [grunts]

662
00:35:07,083 --> 00:35:10,917
- [rocks crashing]

663
00:35:10,959 --> 00:35:16,917
♪

664
00:35:29,250 --> 00:35:34,959
♪

665
00:35:48,542 --> 00:35:49,750
- I can't pin her down.

666
00:35:49,792 --> 00:35:51,250
She's too quick.

667
00:35:51,291 --> 00:35:55,625
♪

668
00:36:00,542 --> 00:36:03,458
- [grunting]

669
00:36:05,959 --> 00:36:09,041
- Wait! Aang, Toph,
stop attacking.

670
00:36:09,083 --> 00:36:10,291
Don't you see what she's doing?

671
00:36:10,333 --> 00:36:11,834
She's just playing with us.

672
00:36:11,875 --> 00:36:13,875
She's not even trying
to win this fight!

673
00:36:13,917 --> 00:36:16,709
- Not true, I'm
giving it my all.

674
00:36:16,750 --> 00:36:19,291
- You're trying to keep us here
and waste all our time!

675
00:36:19,333 --> 00:36:20,709
- Um, right.

676
00:36:20,750 --> 00:36:22,583
I think your friend
just said that genius.

677
00:36:22,625 --> 00:36:23,917
And since you can't see,

678
00:36:23,959 --> 00:36:26,875
I should tell you
I'm rolling my eyes.

679
00:36:26,917 --> 00:36:28,625
- I'll roll your whole head!

680
00:36:28,667 --> 00:36:30,375
- She's just baiting you again.

681
00:36:30,417 --> 00:36:32,041
- Okay, so what do we do?

682
00:36:32,083 --> 00:36:33,542
Just ignore her?

683
00:36:33,583 --> 00:36:36,125
- We don't have a choice,
we just have to get out of here

684
00:36:36,166 --> 00:36:39,166
and find the Fire Lord
on our own somehow.

685
00:36:39,208 --> 00:36:40,208
- It's a trap.

686
00:36:40,250 --> 00:36:41,917
Don't say I didn't warn you.

687
00:36:41,959 --> 00:36:43,917
- Ignore!

688
00:36:43,959 --> 00:36:46,500
- So, Sokka's your name, right?

689
00:36:46,542 --> 00:36:50,208
My favorite prisoner used
to mention you all the time.

690
00:36:50,250 --> 00:36:52,709
She was convinced that you were
going to come rescue her.

691
00:36:52,750 --> 00:36:56,834
Of course, you never came,
and she gave up on you.

692
00:36:56,875 --> 00:37:00,125
- [grunting]

693
00:37:00,166 --> 00:37:01,667
- Come and get it.

694
00:37:01,709 --> 00:37:05,250
- ♪

695
00:37:05,291 --> 00:37:07,959
- [grunts]

696
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:11,000
- Where is Suki?

697
00:37:12,709 --> 00:37:15,041
- After I leave here today,
I'm going to free Uncle Iroh

698
00:37:15,083 --> 00:37:16,250
from his prison.

699
00:37:16,291 --> 00:37:18,375
And I'm going to beg
for his forgiveness.

700
00:37:18,417 --> 00:37:20,625
He is the one who has been
a real father to me.

701
00:37:20,667 --> 00:37:23,250
- [chuckles]
That's just beautiful.

702
00:37:23,291 --> 00:37:26,834
Maybe he can pass down to you
the ways of tea and failure.

703
00:37:26,875 --> 00:37:28,959
- But I've come to an even more
important decision.

704
00:37:30,583 --> 00:37:32,500
I'm going to join the Avatar.

705
00:37:32,542 --> 00:37:34,333
And I'm going to help him
defeat you.

706
00:37:34,375 --> 00:37:35,834
- Really?

707
00:37:35,875 --> 00:37:38,166
Since you're
a full-blown traitor now,

708
00:37:38,208 --> 00:37:40,417
and you want me gone, why wait?

709
00:37:40,458 --> 00:37:43,542
I'm powerless,
you've got your swords,

710
00:37:43,583 --> 00:37:45,625
why don't you just do it now?

711
00:37:45,667 --> 00:37:47,709
- Because I know
my own destiny.

712
00:37:47,750 --> 00:37:50,542
Taking you down
is the Avatar's destiny.

713
00:37:50,583 --> 00:37:52,250
- [metal clangs]

714
00:37:52,291 --> 00:37:54,083
- Goodbye.

715
00:37:54,125 --> 00:37:56,250
- Coward! You think
you're brave enough to face me,

716
00:37:56,291 --> 00:37:58,500
but you'll only do it
during the eclipse.

717
00:37:58,542 --> 00:38:00,375
If you have any real courage,

718
00:38:00,417 --> 00:38:03,291
you'll stick around
until the Sun comes out.

719
00:38:03,333 --> 00:38:06,625
Don't you want to know
what happened to your mother?

720
00:38:06,667 --> 00:38:10,041
- ♪

721
00:38:18,125 --> 00:38:19,917
- What happened that night?

722
00:38:19,959 --> 00:38:23,500
- My father--Fire Lord Azulon--
had commanded me

723
00:38:23,542 --> 00:38:27,667
to do the unthinkable to you,
my own son.

724
00:38:27,709 --> 00:38:29,959
And I was going to do it.

725
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:31,166
Your Mother found out

726
00:38:31,208 --> 00:38:34,291
and swore she would
protect you at any cost.

727
00:38:34,333 --> 00:38:37,834
She knew I wanted the throne,
and she proposed a plan.

728
00:38:37,875 --> 00:38:41,500
A plan in which I would become
Fire Lord

729
00:38:41,542 --> 00:38:45,000
and your life would be spared.

730
00:38:45,041 --> 00:38:47,000
- Where's Suki?

731
00:38:47,041 --> 00:38:48,500
Answer me!

732
00:38:48,542 --> 00:38:52,166
- Sokka, she won't talk.

733
00:38:52,208 --> 00:38:53,625
- Where are you keeping her?

734
00:38:55,083 --> 00:38:58,875
- Your Mother did vicious,
treasonous things that night.

735
00:38:58,917 --> 00:39:01,500
She knew the consequences
and accepted them.

736
00:39:01,542 --> 00:39:05,208
For her treason,
she was banished.

737
00:39:05,250 --> 00:39:06,959
- So she's alive.

738
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:09,166
- Perhaps.

739
00:39:09,208 --> 00:39:13,166
Now I realize that banishment
is far too merciful a penalty

740
00:39:13,208 --> 00:39:14,625
for treason.

741
00:39:14,667 --> 00:39:18,083
Your penalty
will be far steeper.

742
00:39:18,125 --> 00:39:21,250
- ♪

743
00:39:21,291 --> 00:39:26,834
- [lightning zapping]

744
00:39:28,500 --> 00:39:30,875
- [explosion]
- [grunts]

745
00:39:30,917 --> 00:39:36,000
- ♪

746
00:39:39,166 --> 00:39:41,792
- Oh. Sounds like
the fire-bending's back on.

747
00:39:41,834 --> 00:39:45,000
[grunting]

748
00:39:45,041 --> 00:39:48,625
- ♪

749
00:39:51,125 --> 00:39:53,166
- Dad's all the way
at the end of the hall

750
00:39:53,208 --> 00:39:55,000
and down the secret stairway
on the left.

751
00:39:55,041 --> 00:39:58,166
I'm sure he'll be more
than happy to see you now.

752
00:39:58,208 --> 00:39:59,250
- I fell for it!

753
00:39:59,291 --> 00:40:01,375
I used up all our time.

754
00:40:01,417 --> 00:40:03,250
- It's not your fault, Sokka.

755
00:40:03,291 --> 00:40:04,625
Azula was ready for us.

756
00:40:04,667 --> 00:40:07,250
She had every move planned out.

757
00:40:07,291 --> 00:40:09,208
- And now it's too late.

758
00:40:09,250 --> 00:40:11,083
- Maybe it's not too late.

759
00:40:11,125 --> 00:40:14,709
The eclipse is over, but I can
face the Fire Lord anyway.

760
00:40:14,750 --> 00:40:15,750
- No.

761
00:40:15,792 --> 00:40:17,041
I don't think
that's a good idea.

762
00:40:17,083 --> 00:40:18,625
- But I'm ready!

763
00:40:18,667 --> 00:40:21,959
I came here with a job to do,
and everyone's counting on me.

764
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:24,166
- The Fire Lord knew
we were coming this time.

765
00:40:24,208 --> 00:40:26,500
We thought we had surprise
on our side, but we didn't.

766
00:40:26,542 --> 00:40:28,041
It just wasn't our day.

767
00:40:28,083 --> 00:40:31,375
What we need to do now
is go help our friends.

768
00:40:31,417 --> 00:40:32,667
- I guess you guys are right.

769
00:40:32,709 --> 00:40:34,125
- You'll have another chance.

770
00:40:34,166 --> 00:40:35,625
I know you will.

771
00:40:40,667 --> 00:40:42,000
- What should we do, Hakoda?

772
00:40:42,041 --> 00:40:44,041
Shouldn't something
have happened by now?

773
00:40:44,083 --> 00:40:45,291
- I don't know.

774
00:40:45,333 --> 00:40:47,000
But now that the eclipse
is over,

775
00:40:47,041 --> 00:40:50,250
I expect we're going to see
some Firebenders any minute.

776
00:40:50,291 --> 00:40:54,667
- ♪

777
00:40:59,041 --> 00:41:01,333
- My own invention.

778
00:41:01,375 --> 00:41:03,000
Oh, this is terrible!

779
00:41:03,041 --> 00:41:08,709
- ♪

780
00:41:14,667 --> 00:41:16,000
- They're back!

781
00:41:16,041 --> 00:41:21,959
- ♪

782
00:41:30,125 --> 00:41:31,667
- It was all a trap.

783
00:41:31,709 --> 00:41:35,125
Azula knew we were coming, and
she's plotted out every move.

784
00:41:35,166 --> 00:41:37,750
We just got to get to the beach
as fast as we can.

785
00:41:37,792 --> 00:41:38,959
If we can make it
to the submarines,

786
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:40,417
maybe we can get away safely.

787
00:41:40,458 --> 00:41:43,000
- They've got air power,
but so do I!

788
00:41:43,041 --> 00:41:44,792
- ♪

789
00:41:44,834 --> 00:41:46,792
- I'm going to do what I can
to slow them down.

790
00:41:49,834 --> 00:41:52,041
- Appa, you and I can help, too.

791
00:41:52,083 --> 00:41:54,792
- ♪

792
00:41:54,834 --> 00:41:57,083
- Everyone, let's get back
to the subs!

793
00:41:57,125 --> 00:42:02,000
- ♪

794
00:42:15,500 --> 00:42:18,208
- [gunfire exploding]

795
00:42:18,250 --> 00:42:22,917
- [growling]

796
00:42:22,959 --> 00:42:26,667
- ♪

797
00:42:26,709 --> 00:42:28,375
- We can't keep them all back.

798
00:42:28,417 --> 00:42:30,375
They're too many of them!

799
00:42:30,417 --> 00:42:31,834
- Let's join the others.

800
00:42:31,875 --> 00:42:36,750
- ♪

801
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:45,083
- Uncle!

802
00:42:45,125 --> 00:42:50,166
- ♪

803
00:42:50,208 --> 00:42:51,542
- Where is my Uncle?

804
00:42:51,583 --> 00:42:53,208
- He's gone.

805
00:42:53,250 --> 00:42:54,917
He busted himself out.

806
00:42:54,959 --> 00:42:56,750
I--I've never seen
anything like it!

807
00:42:56,792 --> 00:42:59,417
He was like a one man army!

808
00:42:59,458 --> 00:43:05,291
- ♪

809
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:08,000
- Try and find cover!

810
00:43:08,041 --> 00:43:09,917
I think we're about
to see some bombs.

811
00:43:09,959 --> 00:43:14,667
- ♪

812
00:43:16,291 --> 00:43:21,417
- [bombs exploding]

813
00:43:21,458 --> 00:43:23,375
- ♪

814
00:43:23,417 --> 00:43:29,333
- MEN: [screams]

815
00:43:29,375 --> 00:43:32,709
- Why aren't they turning around
to attack us again?

816
00:43:32,750 --> 00:43:35,125
- They're headed for the beach.

817
00:43:35,166 --> 00:43:36,917
They're going to destroy
the submarines!

818
00:43:36,959 --> 00:43:38,542
- How are we all
going to escape?

819
00:43:38,583 --> 00:43:40,959
- We're not.

820
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:43,125
- Then our only choice
is to stand and fight.

821
00:43:43,166 --> 00:43:46,000
We have the Avatar,
we could still win!

822
00:43:46,041 --> 00:43:50,000
- Yes, with the Avatar we could
still win on another day.

823
00:43:50,041 --> 00:43:51,583
You kids have to leave.

824
00:43:51,625 --> 00:43:53,959
You have to escape
on Appa together.

825
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:54,834
- What?

826
00:43:54,875 --> 00:43:56,542
We can't leave you behind.

827
00:43:56,583 --> 00:43:58,792
We won't leave anyone behind.

828
00:43:58,834 --> 00:44:01,125
- You're our only chance
in the long run.

829
00:44:01,166 --> 00:44:03,834
You and Sokka have to go
with Aang somewhere safe.

830
00:44:03,875 --> 00:44:06,250
It's the only way
to keep hope alive.

831
00:44:06,291 --> 00:44:08,750
- The youngest of our group
should go with you.

832
00:44:08,792 --> 00:44:11,500
The adults will stay behind
and surrender.

833
00:44:11,542 --> 00:44:15,583
We'll be prisoners, but we'll
all survive this battle.

834
00:44:15,625 --> 00:44:18,834
- I've got some experience
with the Fire Nation prisons.

835
00:44:18,875 --> 00:44:21,625
It's not going to be easy,
but we'll get by.

836
00:44:21,667 --> 00:44:22,917
- They're at the beach already!

837
00:44:22,959 --> 00:44:27,542
- ♪

838
00:44:33,333 --> 00:44:37,291
- [bombs exploding]

839
00:44:47,125 --> 00:44:51,083
- [explosions continue]

840
00:44:51,125 --> 00:44:56,542
- ♪

841
00:45:03,542 --> 00:45:04,834
- Bye, son.

842
00:45:04,875 --> 00:45:06,250
- Bye, Dad.

843
00:45:06,291 --> 00:45:08,125
I'm really proud of you.

844
00:45:08,166 --> 00:45:11,417
- ♪

845
00:45:11,458 --> 00:45:13,875
- [grunts]
I'll miss you, Pipsqueak.

846
00:45:13,917 --> 00:45:17,542
- Take care, The Duke.

847
00:45:17,583 --> 00:45:19,083
- We'll be back for you, Dad.

848
00:45:19,125 --> 00:45:21,250
- If we don't escape
on our own first.

849
00:45:21,291 --> 00:45:24,542
♪

850
00:45:24,583 --> 00:45:28,000
- We lost today,
but we've never been this close.

851
00:45:28,041 --> 00:45:31,458
We tasted victory,
and that counts for something.

852
00:45:31,500 --> 00:45:34,667
Katara: We'll miss you, Dad.

853
00:45:34,709 --> 00:45:35,959
- Bye, Dad.

854
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:37,875
We won't be apart
for too long this time.

855
00:45:37,917 --> 00:45:39,583
I promise.

856
00:45:39,625 --> 00:45:45,542
♪

857
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:53,792
- Thank you all for being
so brave and so strong.

858
00:45:53,834 --> 00:45:57,875
I'm going to make this
up to you.

859
00:45:57,917 --> 00:46:03,083
- [growling]

860
00:46:03,125 --> 00:46:08,959
♪

861
00:46:12,500 --> 00:46:14,041
- Should we follow them,
Princess?

862
00:46:14,083 --> 00:46:16,083
- No. They're too fast.

863
00:46:16,125 --> 00:46:18,375
It doesn't matter,
they'll be back.

864
00:46:18,417 --> 00:46:21,709
♪

865
00:46:21,750 --> 00:46:23,542
- I know just the place
for us to go

866
00:46:23,583 --> 00:46:24,834
where we'll be safe for a while.

867
00:46:24,875 --> 00:46:26,417
The Western Air Temple.

868
00:46:26,458 --> 00:46:30,750
- [grunting]

869
00:46:30,792 --> 00:46:36,250
♪

870
00:46:48,667 --> 00:46:53,166
- MALE:
[vocalizing drumbeats]
